Use traceroute command with option -m 5 to limit thenumber of hops and make output shorter.

Executable command in Terminal: traceroute -m 5 slash16.org
The output is:

traceroute to slash16.org (13.33.242.162), 5 hops max, 52 byte packets
 1  192.168.30.1 (192.168.30.1)  1.464 ms  0.992 ms  0.989 ms
 2  192.168.2.9 (192.168.2.9)  0.311 ms  0.209 ms  0.321 ms
 3  83-69-219-253.in-addr.mastertelecom.ru (83.69.219.253)  3.379 ms  2.182 ms  2.538 ms
 4  mail.neoresurs.ru (217.67.176.130)  0.604 ms  0.614 ms  0.544 ms
 5  217-67-176-205.in-addr.mastertelecom.ru (217.67.176.205)  1.723 ms  1.578 ms  2.683 ms

The first found device (line 2 output) is the next one after local network on the way to outside.
